Let me tell you about my experience.

Hi AMNA,

My name is Vine and two years ago I was right where you are now – deciding which university to trust with my future.

After receiving offers to study at three different universities, I was struggling to choose which one to accept. There were so many factors to consider like educational culture and areas of expertise, so after researching and asking lots of questions to all three universities, I chose QUT – the university for the real world.

During my two years studying at QUT, I was constantly impressed by how QUT emphasised opportunities that integrated knowledge and learnings into real, high-quality practical applications. Each project or assessment was grounded and embedded with real-world examples, giving real insight into how companies and organisations worked to solve challenges.

But it’s not all about study. I have also worked part-time in hospitality and retail, explored Brisbane, and made lots of friends. The experiences I have gained have helped me to become more independent and confident.

I understand that making the decision to study overseas is a big decision, but it’s also a brave one. My advice? Step outside your comfort zone and challenge yourself.

Best wishes on your journey to QUT!

Vine
Master of Business (Marketing), China

Hi Sanjeev,

Great to hear from you and I’m glad to hear you’re interested in study at QUT! My name is Morgan and I'm here to help answer any questions you may have.

Unfortunately, QUT cannot provide advice on applications to other universities such as USQ, or the Department of Home Affairs. If you have questions regarding your CoE or application process or visa, I would suggest reaching out to USQ directly or to the Department of Home Affairs. You can contact the Department of Home Affairs using one of the following methods:


  *   Website: https://immi.homeaffairs.gov.au/help-support/contact-us<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://immi.homeaffairs.gov.au/help-support/contact-us__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!FptUeFqExT7YZwB-O3FJ_XIN9ngZ5gqoPiIAEKc4dsiDopNUwEMNF5bFbKjcQ9QhS8kDwgBJa2MOziK4CCdvLwDi8hY$>
  *   Phone within Australia: 131 881
  *   Phone outside Australia: +61 2 6196 0196

In regards to scholarships at QUT. All international applicants are automatically considered for the International Merit Scholarship (IMS) once an application has been submitted. The IMS award offers a 25% reduction in tuition fees for the first year of your course at QUT.

For eligible courses only, an ongoing award of 25% per semester may be offered to students who continue to meet the GPA requirement.

For more information, please visit the International Merit Scholarship<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/fees-and-scholarships/scholarships/international-merit-scholarship> webpage.

I believe I have answered all your questions but if you need additional support, you can reply to this email, call us, chat with us, or book a call back<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://bit.ly/3LtsKxj__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!FptUeFqExT7YZwB-O3FJ_XIN9ngZ5gqoPiIAEKc4dsiDopNUwEMNF5bFbKjcQ9QhS8kDwgBJa2MOziK4CCdvwWyAgdM$>.

Hi Suda Alhumaidi M,

Congratulations on your conditional offer to study Master of Business at QUT in Semester 2, 2024!

We are so excited to have you join us and the other thousands of international students in Brisbane. You can accept your offer now by getting in touch with your agent, IGEC (Riyadh). Your agent will help you to meet the conditions on your offer letter.

Find your people at QUT
Whether you are missing home or excited to go on a new adventure there's supportive and exciting communities around every corner at QUT.

Join the QUT surfers club and travel down to the stunning coast of Byron Bay to learn how to surf. If you prefer to surf powder, join the QUT snowsports club and go on their annual trip to NZ to hit the slopes.

There are special interest groups covering bubble tea, anime and manga, burlesque, Minecraft and so much more.

There are also faculty-specific clubs to help you with all things relevant to your degree, and associations for many countries providing support and a sense of home.

No matter what your interests or needs, there is a QUT club to support you. And if there's not - you can always start one!

Hi Gena,

My name is Vine and two years ago I was right where you are now – deciding which university to trust with my future.

After receiving offers to study at three different universities, I was struggling to choose which one to accept. There were so many factors to consider like educational culture and areas of expertise, so after researching and asking lots of questions to all three universities, I chose QUT – the university for the real world.

During my two years studying at QUT, I was constantly impressed by how QUT emphasised opportunities that integrated knowledge and learnings into real, high-quality practical applications. Each project or assessment was grounded and embedded with real-world examples, giving real insight into how companies and organisations worked to solve challenges.

But it’s not all about study. I have also worked part-time in hospitality and retail, explored Brisbane, and made lots of friends. The experiences I have gained have helped me to become more independent and confident.

I understand that making the decision to study overseas is a big decision, but it’s also a brave one. My advice? Step outside your comfort zone and challenge yourself.

Best wishes on your journey to QUT!

Vine
Master of Business (Marketing), China

Find your people at QUT
Whether you are missing home or excited to go on a new adventure there's supportive and exciting communities around every corner at QUT.

Join the QUT surfers club and travel down to the stunning coast of Byron Bay to learn how to surf. If you prefer to surf powder, join the QUT snowsports club and go on their annual trip to NZ to hit the slopes.

There are special interest groups covering bubble tea, anime and manga, burlesque, Minecraft and so much more.

There are also faculty-specific clubs to help you with all things relevant to your degree, and associations for many countries providing support and a sense of home.

No matter what your interests or needs, there is a QUT club to support you. And if there's not - you can always start one!

Let me tell you about my experience.
Hi Scott,

My name is Vine and two years ago I was right where you are now – deciding which university to trust with my future.

After receiving offers to study at three different universities, I was struggling to choose which one to accept. There were so many factors to consider like educational culture and areas of expertise, so after researching and asking lots of questions to all three universities, I chose QUT – the university for the real world.

During my two years studying at QUT, I was constantly impressed by how QUT emphasised opportunities that integrated knowledge and learnings into real, high-quality practical applications. Each project or assessment was grounded and embedded with real-world examples, giving real insight into how companies and organisations worked to solve challenges.

But it’s not all about study. I have also worked part-time in hospitality and retail, explored Brisbane, and made lots of friends. The experiences I have gained have helped me to become more independent and confident.

I understand that making the decision to study overseas is a big decision, but it’s also a brave one. My advice? Step outside your comfort zone and challenge yourself.

Best wishes on your journey to QUT!

Vine
Master of Business (Marketing), China

Subject: Major Promotional Themes for the Spring Education Expo in Taiwan, OH! Study Education Center
Description:
Dear Friends and Colleagues,

Greetings from Taiwan and the OH! Study Education Center!

I am writing to you concerning the upcoming 2024 Spring Overseas Education Expo from March 16th to the 20th in Taipei, Kaohsiung, Taichung and Hsinchu (https://ohstudy.net/expo<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://ohstudy.net/expo__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!Cd4GHzOFM2WOAvnR409Tm9_f64nU8nWyxAiyKY2Vp7yfNhPDoFY2I7U97dspyj3cV3TXthCTaTNsZuG9fL_v$>).

We are expecting well over 100 institutions to participate in the expo, and it will be five major promotional theme for the event.


  1.  Work and career development opportunities during and after overseas education programs.
  2.  A special focus on undergraduate and community college/polytechnic programs
  3.  Everything related to AI and robotics
  4.  Summer programs
  5.  Academic language and test prep programs

More information about these promotions will become available as we get closer to the spring event.  However, we welcome you to contact us to discuss ways we can better promote your school through one of these themes (or even others) during our spring event.

OH! Study consistently hosts the largest overseas education fairs in Taiwan, and is able to attract the largest number of high-quality students through a comprehensive promotions strategy.  We sincerely hope, you will be able to join us in the spring for what promises to be a dynamic and large-scale event.

If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact me or our event management team at expo@ohstudy.net<mailto:expo@ohstudy.net>. We look forward to hosting you in the spring!

Best regards,

Brian Hockertz
President
OH! Study Education Center
Taipei, Taiwan
Brian.hockertz@ohstudy.net<mailto:Brian.hockertz@ohstudy.net>

Special Note from the President – Conflicting Events
It has come to our attention that other organizations have decided to host their spring exhibitions on the same dates as ours.  While we encourage robust and innovative competition, and we respect everyone’s right to conduct their own business, we are concerned this move may be counterproductive and put several of our partnered schools in difficult positions. OH! Study holds its Taipei event in the largest venue in the city, and as such, we must book and pay deposits well over a year in advance, and we announce our dates a year in advance, too. If for whatever reason you are unable to attend our events, we would still be happy to work with you and promote your school and its programs. Of course, if you are able to attend our event, we will be able to more actively promote you.

The 3rd Middle East Education Thought Leadership Forum (METLF)

الملتقى الثالث لريادة الفكر في التعليم في الشرق الأوسط (METLF)


Date: 22-23 November 2023

Venue: Millenium Gloucester Hotel , Kensington, London

Theme: Creativity has no limits! Beyond Concepts: Progressive Educational Transformation.


Audience:

Thought leaders, educators, policymakers, and key stakeholders in the field of education from the Middle East, Africa and beyond.


Background:

The Middle East Education Thought Leadership Forum (METLF) stands as a beacon where the foremost minds come together to sculpt the future of education. The previous METLF events have been monumental platforms, where transformative dialogues and solutions have catalyzed sweeping advancements across several countries. over 3000 people registered for the first METLF online, and a total of 1200 people from 54different countries participated.

Concept:

METLF 2023 will explore how higher education and technology can support the SDGs creatively through four main aspects: ethical considerations, accessibility ,effectiveness, and collaboration. The forum will explore the crucial role of technology in shaping the future of education. Understanding the crucial role ,you and your institution play in shaping education.

The concept will materialize in the presentations, expert and student panels and exclusive workshops included in the tightly packed two-day agenda.


Session Themes:

SESSION 1:Introduction and Keynote

SESSION 2:Artificial Intelligence and Advanced Technology

SESSION 3:Technology, Equity and Accessibility

SESSION 4:Addressing Students’ Needs: A Critical Factor for Enhancing Success

SESSION 5:Addressing the Gender Gap and Empowering Women: Lessons Learned and Best Practices

SESSION 6: What is the role of Quality Assurance Frameworks in our region in supporting the integration of transformative learning for sustainable development?

SESSION 7:Global Learning Innovations and Trends: Challenges and Opportunities

SESSION 8:Technology and Ethics in the 21st century


METLF 2023 Highlights:

• Engage with a global consortium of top-tier educators, practitioners, and policymakers.

• Delve into novel pedagogical strategies emphasizing sustainable learning experiences.

• Explore the avant-garde role of technology, with an emphasis on AI, in modern education.

• Immerse IN diverse sessions spanning workshops, expert panels, and technological showcases.

• Forge invaluable connections with international education mavens during our exhibition.

• Witness the powerful endorsements from the MENA region's eminent education figures.

• Catalyse international synergies, bridging gaps with influential decision-makers and tech trailblazers.

Cost Per Participant £750:

• Participation in all sessions and workshops** during the two-day conference.

• Refreshments during breaks.

• Gourmet lunches with vegetarian and non-vegetarian options.

• Partake in the opulent Gala Dinner on the evening of Wednesday, 22nd November.

•Certificate of attendance for all delegates.

*Concessions for students and group bookings **An additional fee for exclusive workshops

Accommodation:

The Millenium Gloucester Hotel London Kensington,02073736030 or email : Reservations.Gloucester@millenniumhotels.co.uk<mailto:Reservations.Gloucester@millenniumhotels.co.uk> and use the Specials booking code CEDA211123

We look forward to your participation and how we can collaborate to shape the future of global education.

التاريخ: 22-23 نوفمبر 2023

المكان: فندق ميلينيوم غلوستر في كينزينجتون،لندن

الموضوع: الإبداع ليس له حدود! خارج الأفكار: تحول تعليمي متقدم.



الجمهور:

رواد الفكر، والمعلمون،وصانعو السياسات، وأصحاب المصلحة الرئيسيين في مجال التعليم من منطقة الشرق الأوسط وأفريقيا وما وراءهما.


الخلفية:

يعتبر منتدى التعليم منارة في التعليم والابتكار، يقف الملتقى الثالث لريادة الفكر في التعليم في الشرق الأوسط (METLF) كمصباح يجتمع فيه أمهر العقول لنحت مستقبل التعليم. شهدت الأحداث السابقة لـMETLF منصات ضخمة حيث تم توجيه حوارات وحلول محورية أسهمت في تحقيق تقدم هائل في عدة دول. تم تسجيل أكثر من 3000شخص في أول حدث METLF عبر الإنترنت، وشارك مجموعه1200 شخص من 54 دولة مختلفة. أُقيم الملتقى الثاني لـMETLF في لندن في عام 2022 وأثبت نجاحًا كبيرًا بمشاركة الوزراء والقادة المرموقين بما في ذلك السفراء بما في ذلك صاحب السمو الملكي الأمير خالد بن بندر، سفير المملكة العربية السعودية في المملكةالمتحدة.


المفهوم:


سيستكشف METLF 2023 كيفيمكن للتعليم العالي والتكنولوجيا دعم أهداف التنمية المستدامة بإبداع من خلال أربعة جوانب رئيسية: الاعتبارات الأخلاقية، والوصول، والفعالية،والتعاون. سيكشف الملتقى الدور الحاسم للتكنولوجيا في تشكيل مستقبل التعليم، مع التركيز على الدور الحاسم الذي تلعبه أنت ومؤسستك في تشكيل التعليم.

سيتم تجسيدهذا المفهوم في العروض واللوحات الخبرية ولوحات الطلاب وورش العمل الحصرية المدرجةفي جدول الأعمال المكثف ليومين.


موضوعات الجلسات:


الجلسة 1: المقدمة والمحاضرة الرئيسية

الجلسة 2: الذكاء الاصطناعيوالتكنولوجيا المتقدمة

الجلسة 3: التكنولوجيا والعدالة والوصول

الجلسة 4: تلبية احتياجات الطلاب: عامل حاسم لتعزيز النجاح

الجلسة 5: التصدي لفجوة النوع وتمكين النساء: الدروس المستفادة وأفضل الممارسات

الجلسة 6: ما هو دور أطُر الضمان النوعي في منطقتنا في دعم دمج التعلم التحولي من أجل التنمية المستدامة؟

الجلسة 7: الابتكارات والاتجاهات العالمية في التعلم: التحديات والفرص

الجلسة 8: التكنولوجيا والأخلاق في القرن 21



ملامح METLF 2023:


• اشترك مع كوكبة عالمية من أعلى المعلمين والممارسين وصانعيالسياسات.

• استكشف استراتيجيات تربوية جديدة تؤكد تجارب التعلم المستدامة.

• اغمر نفسك في الدور الريادي للتكنولوجيا، مع التركيز علىالذكاء الاصطناعي، في التعليم الحديث.

• شارك في جلسات متنوعة تشمل ورش العمل ولوحات الخبراء وعروضالتكنولوجيا.

• قم ببناء اتصالات قيمة مع خبراء التعليم الدوليين خلال معرضنا.

Description:
ZjQcmQRYFpfptBannerEnd
Dear QUT,
I am writing to ask for information about your English language requirements. I wanted to take IELTS exam this month, but this test is no longer available in my country. There are different ways to take English test as it mentioned in requirements part but unfortunately neither of them are available in Iran. 
I have looked at your website, but there is no information about Duolingo test. Could you please send me information if I can take Duolingo test instead of other ones? If the answer is yes, I would also like to know the Duolingo score you accept. 
According to the time I have to apply for this semester to begin study Project Management, I would be appreciated if you accept Duolingo English test too. 
I look forward to hearing from you.
Sincerely,
Saeedeh ( Misha ) Hosseinzadeh

Subject: Enquiries about Accepting the Unconditional Offer
Description:
Dear International Future Students Team,


I am an international future exchange student from Hong Kong (QUT student number: 11933046). I would like to accept the unconditional offer; however, I have some enquiries about this procedure.


Firstly, the accepting offer procedure has a question “Which Australian Embassy will you lodge your student visa application at?” but I will apply for the student visa online. Hence, I don’t know whether I should fill in Hong Kong or Australia.


Secondly, I had indicated that I was organising my own OSHC in my application. However, I would like to change the option and select and pay for the OSHC organised by QUT during the accepting offer procedure. Is it okay? Also, after I pay for the OSHC, will there be any official letter issued to me?


Thirdly, the offer letter has not mentioned that any English Language Course is required for me. Does that mean I don’t need to study English Language Course during my exchange?


I look forward to hearing from you soon. Thank you.



Best regards,

Cathy Ng

Description:
Subject: Request for Information on Work Study Programs at the Queensland University of Technology (QUT) 
Dear, I am writing this letter to express my keen interest in the work study programs offered by the Queensland University of Technology (QUT). 
As a potential candidate, I am deeply excited to explore these work-study opportunities at a reputable institution such as yours.
Currently a final-year Computer Network engineering student at  New Higher School of Engineering and Technology (ENSIT), I am determined to deepen my learning by combining my academic studies with practical work experience.
I was impressed by QUT's reputation as a leading higher education institution and its long history of commitment to educational excellence. I am particularly interested in the work study programs at QUT because of the technology project management.
I firmly believe that this opportunity would allow me to gain valuable professional experience while continuing my academic studies.
I would like more information about the work study programs offered by QUT, including eligibility criteria, application procedures, and opportunities available in my field of study.
I would be grateful if you could direct me to any resources or provide me with details on how to apply for work study programs at QUT. Thank you for your attention to my request. I am open to further discussions and willing to take all necessary steps to explore this exciting opportunity within your institution.
 
 
 
Sincerely, 
Faustin YOUH

Here's how to accept and join us at QUT
Accepting your offer to study will be exciting and a little daunting at first. Here is a list of what happens next so you can feel prepared and ready to take on this next journey with confidence.

  *   Officially accept your offer. Don't forget to pay your deposit as we won't be able to process your acceptance until we have received your payment. You'll need to contact your agent to complete this step.
  *   We will aim to process your acceptance within 5 business days and provide your agent with your Confirmation of Enrolment Certificate (eCOE).
  *   When you are accepted, you can access a whole range of great resources to get you started at QUT, including enrolment guides, class registration instructions, timetable planning, support and more!

Getting prepared to come to Australia
Moving to a new country is an exciting journey, and there’s lots to organise before you take off. Before you leave, make sure you have:

  *   Accepted your offer and paid your fees
  *   Applied for your student visa
  *   Purchased overseas student health cover (OSHC)
  *   Enrolled into your course at QUT
  *   Packed your identity documents
  *   Arranged airport pick-up
  *   Organised your accommodation
  *   Purchased some Australian currency
  *   Booked your flight ticket!

Getting prepared ❯ <https://click.connectme.qut.edu.au/?qs=ef775496f09c9982c93be37f220c6ab187cc40f9d66b47f4f516f25fc635de5cd8438c624295bdb45fe3dfff858d5a7d696861ca3a287f95>

Your home away from home
QUT is ideally located within walking distance from some incredible accommodation options.

You can choose from student residential complexes, residential colleges, or agent-operated student accommodation with a bed and study desk. Bathrooms, kitchens, and common rooms are usually shared.

If you need help finding somewhere to live, our accommodation services<https://click.connectme.qut.edu.au/?qs=ef775496f09c998264c200e01aa65854413cf7cb88f19974e1b21cc596ce329f304c979a79883407e42e2ea055a75ca918747d888421526a> can help you.

Can't see the images? View as webpage.<https://view.connectme.qut.edu.au/?qs=d6422ce604b57e3bc4293bda231ddd30b8dfe3fb5e622acf34d99a63e741c3e714afac08d09c2a0693605d7e64f46bd0c6991f510f67e2f6db5a5e5f35bea13f313435bc1f579dbfa303cfabff52ce3b>
[QUT logo]
[QUT City]
Let me tell you about my experience.
Hi DOMINGOS,

My name is Vine and two years ago I was right where you are now – deciding which university to trust with my future.

After receiving offers to study at three different universities, I was struggling to choose which one to accept. There were so many factors to consider like educational culture and areas of expertise, so after researching and asking lots of questions to all three universities, I chose QUT – the university for the real world.

During my two years studying at QUT, I was constantly impressed by how QUT emphasised opportunities that integrated knowledge and learnings into real, high-quality practical applications. Each project or assessment was grounded and embedded with real-world examples, giving real insight into how companies and organisations worked to solve challenges.

But it’s not all about study. I have also worked part-time in hospitality and retail, explored Brisbane, and made lots of friends. The experiences I have gained have helped me to become more independent and confident.

I understand that making the decision to study overseas is a big decision, but it’s also a brave one. My advice? Step outside your comfort zone and challenge yourself.

Best wishes on your journey to QUT!

Vine
Master of Business (Marketing), China

You have an offer with QUT! 🎉
Hi Sanskriti,

Congratulations on your conditional offer to study Bachelor of Engineering (Honours) at QUT in Semester 2, 2024!

We are so excited to have you join us and the other thousands of international students in Brisbane. You can accept your offer now by getting in touch with your agent, IDP Mumbai Dadar. Your agent will help you to meet the conditions on your offer letter.

Remember to accept early so you leave plenty of time to organise everything before classes start.
Email your agent ❯ <mailto:info.mumbai3@idp.com?subject=Application%20enquiry>
[https://image.connectme.qut.edu.au/lib/fe3111717164067d761d76/m/1/feb87eb5-672e-4153-b35b-08a94140cec5.jpg]
Find your people at QUT
Whether you are missing home or excited to go on a new adventure there's supportive and exciting communities around every corner at QUT.

Join the QUT surfers club and travel down to the stunning coast of Byron Bay to learn how to surf. If you prefer to surf powder, join the QUT snowsports club and go on their annual trip to NZ to hit the slopes.

There are special interest groups covering bubble tea, anime and manga, burlesque, Minecraft and so much more.

There are also faculty-specific clubs to help you with all things relevant to your degree, and associations for many countries providing support and a sense of home.

No matter what your interests or needs, there is a QUT club to support you. And if there's not - you can always start one!

Subject: Study invitation: your opinion about peer review
Description:
Dear colleague,

We trust this message finds you well.

We are conducting a large-scale investigation about peer review practices in social sciences across the world, and we would like to invite you to participate to our survey.

The survey
In particular, in this survey we are interested in your personal experience and opinions about the way peer review for scientific articles is currently implemented in your discipline. Who reviews what, when, and how? Who is (not) invited to review? We are interested in your opinions even if you have never been invited to peer review an article. The survey should take approximately 20 minutes to complete. All data will be processed anonymously, and your contact and personal information will not be made available in any shape or form.

Participant selection
We have sampled participants, including yourself, following a stratified multi-stage procedure: in fifty countries, we have selected 10 universities per country and then identified scholars working in any social sciences department (broadly understood) based on publicly available information on these universities’ websites.

General project
This survey is part of a broader multi-year research project looking at multiple aspects of peer review in social sciences, being undertaken by a team of scholars in eight countries. More information can be found on the project’s website<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://www.peerreviewstudy.com__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!DGXUMdXOUWG9q5O80nlxMhd6DjzcZMkFyWEc5Azjluh2VaymOqte6HPz361mzQ9BmKaZKxuPpghv5ab0mREFUYO3IA$>.


Follow this link to take the survey: Take the Survey<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://uvacommscience.eu.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_7U67qSR8EC53Q4m?Q_DL=EeO7Q4FL5eUMvlZ_7U67qSR8EC53Q4m_CGC_IDCJb059kRep7Qo&Q_CHL=email__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!DGXUMdXOUWG9q5O80nlxMhd6DjzcZMkFyWEc5Azjluh2VaymOqte6HPz361mzQ9BmKaZKxuPpghv5ab0mREIBFseWA$>

Let me tell you about my experience.

Hi Malavika,

My name is Vine and two years ago I was right where you are now – deciding which university to trust with my future.

After receiving offers to study at three different universities, I was struggling to choose which one to accept. There were so many factors to consider like educational culture and areas of expertise, so after researching and asking lots of questions to all three universities, I chose QUT – the university for the real world.

During my two years studying at QUT, I was constantly impressed by how QUT emphasised opportunities that integrated knowledge and learnings into real, high-quality practical applications. Each project or assessment was grounded and embedded with real-world examples, giving real insight into how companies and organisations worked to solve challenges.

But it’s not all about study. I have also worked part-time in hospitality and retail, explored Brisbane, and made lots of friends. The experiences I have gained have helped me to become more independent and confident.

I understand that making the decision to study overseas is a big decision, but it’s also a brave one. My advice? Step outside your comfort zone and challenge yourself.

Best wishes on your journey to QUT!

Vine
Master of Business (Marketing), China

Hi Jimena,

Great to hear from you and I’m glad to hear you’re interested in study at QUT! My name is Morgan and I'm here to help answer any questions you may have.

Our Master of Robotics and Artificial Intelligence<https://www.qut.edu.au/courses/master-of-robotics-and-artificial-intelligence> commences in February of each academic year and runs for 1.5 years full-time from our Gardens Point campus. The annual international tuition fee is approximately $41,700 (2024 AUD fees).

To view the entry requirements<https://www.qut.edu.au/courses/master-of-robotics-and-artificial-intelligence?international#requirements>, visit the course page and scroll down to the ‘Explore this course’ section and click on the ‘Requirements’ tab.

Additional requirements include:

  *   A completed recognised four-year full time Bachelor degree in Engineering in one of the following fields or equialvent: Computer and Software Systems, Electrical, Aerospace, Electronics or Mechatronics with a GPA minimum of 4.0 (on QUT's 7-point scale).

Accommodation and living in Brisbane
During your first weeks in Brisbane, you should budget for approximately $2,500AUD to get yourself set-up in your accommodation, stock up on food and organise your transport card. After that, you can budget for approximately $500 a week for rent, food, transport, utility bills and entertainment.

You’ll find a wide range of accommodation options<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/student-life/living-in-brisbane/accommodation-in-brisbane?international> to suit all budgets within walking distance to either campus. QUT has a dedicated accommodation support service<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/qut.studystays.com.au/__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CHlKcaajZa80ZbH5aBkKUe-qOjWeU2Xs55OGqtR33Y8rZSwIQbmSo9HVUirkTMqLb6Q6F4qux7h43tG_REehMUgB$> to help you navigate the rental market and get you settled into life in Brisbane.

You can read more about Living in Brisbane<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/student-life/living-in-brisbane?international> on the website.

I believe I have answered all your questions but if you need additional support, you can reply to this email, call us, chat with us, or book a call back<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/bit.ly/3LtsKxj__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CHlKcaajZa80ZbH5aBkKUe-qOjWeU2Xs55OGqtR33Y8rZSwIQbmSo9HVUirkTMqLb6Q6F4qux7h43tG_RIXVlS68$>.

[Text    Description automatically generated with low confidence]





Hi Chirag,

Great to hear from you and I’m glad to hear you’re interested in study at QUT! My name is Morgan and I'm here to help answer any questions you may have.

Our Master of Business<https://www.qut.edu.au/courses/master-of-business?international> commences in February and July of each academic year and runs for 1.5 - 2 years full-time from our Gardens Point campus. The annual international tuition fee is approximately $34,000 (2023 AUD fees).

To view the entry requirements<https://www.qut.edu.au/courses/master-of-business?international#requirements>, visit the course page and scroll down to the ‘Explore this course’ section and click on the ‘Requirements’ tab.

  *   1.5 year program: A completed recognised bachelor degree in business or related field with a minimum grade point average (GPA) of 4.00 (on QUT's 7 point scale).
  *   2 year program: A completed recognised bachelor degree in any discipline with a minimum grade point average (GPA) of 4.00 (on QUT's 7 point scale).

If you are unsure whether you meet these entry requirements, we would encourage you to still apply for this course and our international admission team will assess your eligibility once you have submitted a formal application. We cannot pre-assess qualifications.

Credit for prior learning
To be considered for credit towards your QUT course and be able to graduate sooner, you will need to include additional supporting documents with your application. This includes:


  *   your official academic transcript showing the unit code(s), unit title(s) and grade(s) achieved
  *   documents proving that you have completed your course, such as a completion certificate
  *   unit outlines or course syllabus of the unit(s) you are wanting credit for.

There is a question within the application called “Do you wish to be considered for Advanced Standing based on your previous studies?”. You will need to select ‘Yes’ to this question.

Once you have finished and submitted your application, our international admission team will consider your request for advanced standing. Details of the credit awarded and the potential reduction in course duration will be listed in your QUT offer letter. We cannot pre-assess credit – you must apply to QUT with your supporting documents for consideration.

You can search for previously approved units<https://www.advancedstanding.qut.edu.au/cgi-bin/WebObjects/AdvStand.woa> for credit on the Advanced Standing Precedent List.

Scholarships
All international applicants are automatically considered for the International Merit Scholarship (IMS) once an application has been submitted. The IMS award offers a 25% reduction in tuition fees for the first year of your course at QUT.

For eligible courses only, an ongoing award of 25% per semester may be offered to students who continue to meet the GPA requirement.

For more information, please visit the International Merit Scholarship<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/fees-and-scholarships/scholarships/international-merit-scholarship> webpage.

Applying to QUT
You must apply to QUT via an authorised QUT representative (agent). To find an agent, search our database<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/international/find-a-representative> for representatives in your country. An agent can assist you with your application, eligibility and supporting documents and answer any questions you may have about studying at QUT.

You will need to include all your supporting documents including:

  *   High school completion certificate / academic transcripts and records
  *   English language proficiency test results
  *   Passport identity page

I believe I have answered all your questions but if you need additional support, you can reply to this email, call us, chat with us, or book a call back<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://bit.ly/3LtsKxj__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!BSmu6MAfp6_F_isTiQb3Y86S4rNnGtmagB_Vh8n0I7--H8MkZ0OD1LoHpGdnd2AcsnzkP5YE-93q_fKJXvEHSUFMcGwmEL9V$>.

Kind regards,

Subject: Application enquiry
Description:
Dear teachers:

My name is Lu-nung, Chiang (student number:11927747)

I am genuinely thrilled to have received an offer from QUT, which is my dream university. Currently, I find myself in a significant dilemma. The University of Western Australia (UWA) offers me a $10,000 scholarship annually, and Griffith University offers a 25% tuition fee reduction. These offers are undeniably attractive, especially for me and my family's financial situation.

However, in comparison, I have a stronger preference for the warm climate of Brisbane, the campus culture at QUT, the practicality of the courses, and the industry recognition of QUT. Therefore, I would like to inquire if there is a possibility of receiving a partial scholarship from QUT.

(My undergraduate GPA is 3.55 out of 4 with an average of 83.67).

I am committed to showcasing my best self in the coming two years.
Thank you for your consideration and I am looking forward to your response.

Thank you and my sincerest blessings,
Lu-nung. [表情圖示]

Subject: Re: Thanks for your interest in QUT
Description:
Dear sir /Madam
Queensland University Of Technology

I hope you're doing well. I wanted to shoot you an email to let you know how interested I am in studying fashion-related pattern making and drafting at QUT. I've got a bit of a unique background—I actually had a study gap of 13 years, but during that time, I gained some valuable experience working as a salesman at an outdoor clothing store for 5 years. After that, I took the leap and started my own manufacturing business.

I believe that QUT's Bachelor of Design (Fashion) program would be the perfect opportunity for me to enhance my skills and knowledge in garment construction, pattern making, and textile design. I'm really excited about the prospect of joining the QUT community and learning from the best in the field.

If you could provide me with more information about the program, including any admission requirements and application deadlines, I would be incredibly grateful. I'm eager to take this next step in my journey and I truly believe that QUT can help me achieve my goals.

Thank you so much for your time and consideration. I'm looking forward to hearing from you soon!

Best regards,
Manoj Khadka

Hi Pete,



Great to hear from you and I’m glad to hear you’re interested in study at QUT! My name is Morgan and I'm here to help answer any questions you may have.



To explore the study options<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/international> available at QUT, head to our webpage. I have also attached the International Course Guide to help you decide which course is best for you.



International Student Visa holders cannot get an offer to study online/part-time and are required to comply with the requirements of their visas. This often requires the completion of the degree to be in-person and full-time. For more information regarding visa-related matters please contact the Department of Home Affairs<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://immi.homeaffairs.gov.au/help-support/contact-us__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!GLYdclUr_kJDe2GO6vnbyDgfHkXGN3ZhPZG63Gc_xL2JRJEtkzIn2FnJv17GJ7Ufpu1CGlbVMgiPme9Sqtd-p-AcCg$>.

Response By Email (Bibbi) (10/11/2023 04.53 PM)


Hi Pete,

Thank you for your email, it is exciting that you want to study with us at QUT. I can certainly help you with your enquiry regarding entry requirements and study mode options.


Study mode eligibility
Since you classify as a domestic student with your permanent residency you will be able to undertake any mode of delivery that is outlined as available on the domestic students page for that course, including part-time and online mode. Just make sure to check that the course you are interested in have those delivery options available and outlined on the course page because some courses do not have that option.


Conversion of result through the application process
When you apply to an undergraduate course at QUT the application is handled by the Queensland Tertiary Admissions Office<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://www.qtac.edu.au/international-applications/__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!Dxuyc8qV9_loObpMTVHPa22NLUfw857Q5MdTjJOQIVbjtKI3jZM6hDhYEL3E5On6Ffb5wibDJYTHhxkGsIbbEdY$> and they convert your international results (presumably A Levels or IB in your case) into an ATAR/selection rank so that they can asses you in line with the other domestic students eligibility.

If you would like to have a look yourself we have a page called Recent secondary education<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/applying/recent-secondary-education#converting-your-results-to-a-selection-rank>, and there you can find conversion tables for all the variations of International secondary levels qualifications we accept in domestic students, and what the scores in those systems will transfer to in conversion to ATAR/selection rank.


Entry requirements
We also want to make you aware that on the domestic courses pages under the requirements tab there will be listed either 'assumed knowledge' or Prerequisites. Some of our courses have prerequisite subjects instead of, or in addition to, assumed knowledge. Prerequisites means you must have studied and met the required grade in the required subjects to gain entry to these courses. In regards to Assumed Knowledge it is important to note that not having this subject knowledge will not prevent you from gaining entry into the course. However, we recommend having the assumed knowledge so that you can be in the best position to succeed in your degree.

For information on how you can meet the assumed knowledge and whether your subjects meet the prerequisites, you may wish to see our assumed knowledge and prerequisites<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/applying/assumed-knowledge-and-prerequisites> page.

If you should find yourself in a position where you do not meet the assumed knowledge criteria, but you would like to close that knowledge gap, we encourage you to look into our QUT bridging programs<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/bridging-programs>.

Applying
Domestic applicants apply online via the Queensland Tertiary Admissions Centre (QTAC)<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://www.qtac.edu.au/applications/__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!Dxuyc8qV9_loObpMTVHPa22NLUfw857Q5MdTjJOQIVbjtKI3jZM6hDhYEL3E5On6Ffb5wibDJYTHhxkGGAfRBjg$>. QTAC will then assess your eligibility for the course and you may receive an offer to study at QUT. To be considered in the main offer round on the 11th of January 2024, you will need to submit your application and supporting documentation by the 8th of December 2023. The QTAC Key Dates<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://www.qtac.edu.au/key-dates/__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!Dxuyc8qV9_loObpMTVHPa22NLUfw857Q5MdTjJOQIVbjtKI3jZM6hDhYEL3E5On6Ffb5wibDJYTHhxkGlhgW3iQ$> page has a full list of other offer rounds and application due dates. For more information about how to apply, you may also like to refer to the QUT undergraduate applying guide<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/applying/undergraduate-guide>.



Hopefully I have answered all your enquiries, but if there’s anything else we can help you with, please reply to this email, call us on (07) 3138 2000, visit us on campus<http://www.qut.edu.au/student-centres> or start an online chat<http://www.qut.edu.au/student-centres>.

Your enquiry reference number is: 231110-000656.

Kind regards,

Bibbi

Let me tell you about my experience.
Hi Frederick,

My name is Vine and two years ago I was right where you are now – deciding which university to trust with my future.

After receiving offers to study at three different universities, I was struggling to choose which one to accept. There were so many factors to consider like educational culture and areas of expertise, so after researching and asking lots of questions to all three universities, I chose QUT – the university for the real world.

During my two years studying at QUT, I was constantly impressed by how QUT emphasised opportunities that integrated knowledge and learnings into real, high-quality practical applications. Each project or assessment was grounded and embedded with real-world examples, giving real insight into how companies and organisations worked to solve challenges.

But it’s not all about study. I have also worked part-time in hospitality and retail, explored Brisbane, and made lots of friends. The experiences I have gained have helped me to become more independent and confident.

I understand that making the decision to study overseas is a big decision, but it’s also a brave one. My advice? Step outside your comfort zone and challenge yourself.

Best wishes on your journey to QUT!

Vine
Master of Business (Marketing), China

You have an offer with QUT! 🎉
Hi Parasbhai,

Congratulations on your conditional offer to study Master of Professional Engineering at QUT in Semester 1, 2024!

We are so excited to have you join us and the other thousands of international students in Brisbane. You can accept your offer now by getting in touch with your agent, KC Overseas Education. Your agent will help you to meet the conditions on your offer letter.

Remember to accept early so you leave plenty of time to organise everything before classes start.

[X]
Find your people at QUT
Whether you are missing home or excited to go on a new adventure there's supportive and exciting communities around every corner at QUT.

Join the QUT surfers club and travel down to the stunning coast of Byron Bay to learn how to surf. If you prefer to surf powder, join the QUT snowsports club and go on their annual trip to NZ to hit the slopes.

There are special interest groups covering bubble tea, anime and manga, burlesque, Minecraft and so much more.

There are also faculty-specific clubs to help you with all things relevant to your degree, and associations for many countries providing support and a sense of home.

No matter what your interests or needs, there is a QUT club to support you. And if there's not - you can always start one!

Get to know your university at Welcome Week
Getting started at a new university, a new city and a new country all at the same time can be very overwhelming. That's why we have an orientation program especially for international students. You will be able to attend an orientation session built for international students associated with your particular course or program. University-wide orientation events will also help you prepare for your studies.
Start your orientation now ❯ <https://click.connectme.qut.edu.au/?qs=6091d10cb20b96912dca45e5aa2711e1570cd6ec7f1a10adfc3a412363f17debd2c008b6c82f9b5b0048e083db4c87b5d22933e3b269423e>

We can't wait to welcome you to QUT
It 's always nice to see a friendly face when arriving at a new destination, which is why we provide a free 24-hour airport reception and transfer service for new international students.

Whether you land at Brisbane International or Domestic Airport, you can arrive knowing you have a pre-arranged transport service in place to get you to your temporary or permanent accommodation.

Hi,

I'm inquiring about enrolling in a program for the upcoming semester in February. I'm reaching out on behalf of my brother, who is planning to enroll at QUT.

I have a couple of questions regarding his enrollment.

Firstly, my brother is interested in studying the Bachelor of Fine Art (Film, Screen, and New Media). However, his IELTS score is 6.0 overall, and his CSAT (South Korea) aggregate level is 18. Therefore, we are considering starting with a diploma in creative industries and then transferring to the Bachelor of Fine Art in the second year. Could you please confirm if the total duration of the course will still be 3 years?

Secondly, I am assisting my brother with the program application and also the visa application process. I would appreciate your advice on whether it's advisable to proceed with an agency.

Thank you for your assistance.

Sydnee Nam

You have an offer with QUT! 🎉
Hi Prerna Mohan,

Congratulations on your conditional offer to study Master of Data Analytics at QUT in Semester 1, 2024!

We are so excited to have you join us and the other thousands of international students in Brisbane. You can accept your offer now by getting in touch with your agent, KC Overseas Education. Your agent will help you to meet the conditions on your offer letter.

Remember to accept early so you leave plenty of time to organise everything before classes start.
Email your agent ❯ <mailto:australia5@studies-overseas.com?subject=Application%20enquiry>
[https://image.connectme.qut.edu.au/lib/fe3111717164067d761d76/m/1/feb87eb5-672e-4153-b35b-08a94140cec5.jpg]
Find your people at QUT
Whether you are missing home or excited to go on a new adventure there's supportive and exciting communities around every corner at QUT.

Join the QUT surfers club and travel down to the stunning coast of Byron Bay to learn how to surf. If you prefer to surf powder, join the QUT snowsports club and go on their annual trip to NZ to hit the slopes.

There are special interest groups covering bubble tea, anime and manga, burlesque, Minecraft and so much more.

There are also faculty-specific clubs to help you with all things relevant to your degree, and associations for many countries providing support and a sense of home.

No matter what your interests or needs, there is a QUT club to support you. And if there's not - you can always start one!

Bennno, you're just a few steps away from studying with us.
When you apply to QUT, you’re joining a safe and welcoming community of learners, creators, designers, builders, and carers. Build friendships that will last a lifetime and networks that will make you unstoppable in your future career.

With just 6 quick steps, you can start, complete, and submit your application in the time it takes you to get from A to B on your daily commute. And, if you don’t quite finish it in time, you can save your progress and come back to it later.

Here are our top 4 application tips:

  1.  Know which QUT course you want to apply for
  2.  Make sure you meet the entry requirements or ask to be considered for a pathway program
  3.  Have your supporting documents ready to upload
  4.  Submit, sit-back and relax while we process your application

Dear Sir/Madam,

I hope this message finds you well. I am writing to request the university's consideration for a waiver of the English Package ( EAP standard 2 course commencing from 20 November 2023) associated with my Bachelor's degree. While I understand the importance of language proficiency, I have a strong foundation in English, having studied it as a core subject throughout my school years.

The English courses I am currently enrolled in were necessitated by the results of an ad hoc language test, and I believe that my proficiency is sufficient for the academic demands of my chosen course. As an international student, my initial days here pose financial challenges, making it difficult to cover the additional expense of the English Package moreover, I am still not comfortable and could not adjust with the places and foods here which made my health weak.

Granting a waiver would significantly alleviate our financial strain, allowing me to focus more on my studies and contribute positively to my academic experience in Australia. I appreciate your understanding and consideration of this request.

Thank you for your time and attention to this matter.


--
Best regards

Hi Shiny,

Great to hear from you and I’m glad to hear you’re interested in study at QUT! My name is Morgan and I'm here to help answer any questions you may have.

Our Master of Clinical Psychology<https://www.qut.edu.au/courses/master-of-clinical-psychology> commences in February of each academic year and runs for 2 years full-time from our Kelvin Grove campus. The annual international tuition fee is approximately $33,300 (2024 AUD fees).

To view the entry requirements<https://www.qut.edu.au/courses/master-of-clinical-psychology?international#requirements>, visit the course page and scroll down to the ‘Explore this course’ section and click on the ‘Requirements’ tab.

Additional requirements include:

  *   A recognised completed psychology honours or 4-year bachelor degree (or higher) in psychology completed within the last 10 years (2014 or later); and
  *   A minimum fourth year psychology units grade point average (GPA) of 6.00 (on QUT's 7 point scale) in your psychology bachelor degree; and
  *   Your degree must be accredited by the Australian Psychology Accreditation Council (APAC) as a 4-year training (or equivalent) program.
  *   If you have an overseas qualifications you must provide certification with your application from the Australian Psychological Society (APS) stating your degree is equivalent to an APAC-approved, 4-year training in psychology.

I believe I have answered all your questions but if you need additional support, you can reply to this email, call us, chat with us, or book a call back<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://bit.ly/3LtsKxj__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!GhL93VXzdL5PscKuNLZ8epZQRumwjdanmVuHGROh0L6BdxeTQnRNV9aTcJoRIL21pN6LHGz-Y6zxkGNLR-mZU0DM3Gg$>.

Don't delay your dreams!

Start online and come when you can

Studying at QUT is one of the best decisions you'll ever make. You can start your course online in July this year (Semester 2, 2020) without delaying your career plans.

Start online and come on campus when you can.

While the Australian border is closed, we recommend you initially study online with QUT and then come to Brisbane to study on-campus when you can.

Find out more about Semester 2, 2020 study at QUT ❯<http://links.realworld.qut.edu.au/ctt?ms=NjQ2ODgxODUS1&kn=10&r=MzUzNDI2NTU2NjA4S0&b=0&j=MTg4MDk1Njc2NgS2&mt=1&rt=0>
[QUT building]

QUT innovates in response to COVID-19

While we have certainly experienced our share of disruption caused by COVID-19, Australia has fared well<http://links.realworld.qut.edu.au/ctt?ms=NjQ2ODgxODUS1&kn=3&r=MzUzNDI2NTU2NjA4S0&b=0&j=MTg4MDk1Njc2NgS2&mt=1&rt=0> compared to other developed nations, like the UK and US. Australia’s quick action, low population density and strong healthcare system has ensured our comparatively low infection and mortality rate.

QUT professors, researchers and alumni have also contributed to curbing the spread of the virus by working hard to provide innovative solutions to COVID-19-related problems. Below are some great contributions by QUT:

  *   The Creative Industries Faculty has created thousands of facemasks<http://links.realworld.qut.edu.au/ctt?ms=NjQ2ODgxODUS1&kn=31&r=MzUzNDI2NTU2NjA4S0&b=0&j=MTg4MDk1Njc2NgS2&mt=1&rt=0> using their 3D printer
  *   QUT Science and Engineering Faculty alumnus, Mark Dutton, has repurposed his knowledge of Supercars to designing ventilator systems for patients<http://links.realworld.qut.edu.au/ctt?ms=NjQ2ODgxODUS1&kn=6&r=MzUzNDI2NTU2NjA4S0&b=0&j=MTg4MDk1Njc2NgS2&mt=1&rt=0>
  *   QUT researchers are also assisting in developing a vaccine<http://links.realworld.qut.edu.au/ctt?ms=NjQ2ODgxODUS1&kn=21&r=MzUzNDI2NTU2NjA4S0&b=0&j=MTg4MDk1Njc2NgS2&mt=1&rt=0> for the virus by sharing their valuable research

Read more ❯<http://links.realworld.qut.edu.au/ctt?ms=NjQ2ODgxODUS1&kn=7&r=MzUzNDI2NTU2NjA4S0&b=0&j=MTg4MDk1Njc2NgS2&mt=1&rt=0>
[QUT building]

Nursing alumni Yike helps out in troubled times

Bachelor of Nursing alumni Yike Gao is currently making a difference by working as a nurse at the National Corona virus Helpline. She is providing professional medical advice over the phone and educate people about COVID-19.

"My degree from QUT have provided me with strong medical knowledge and real-world experience that has been very useful. During my degree I did my work experience in an infectious disease ward at the hospital. This has given me great understanding of disease control and prevention and of how things work in a clinical setting which has been very beneficial especially in this new job.

It’s very rewarding and a privilege for me to utilise the skills I’ve learnt at university and to contribute to societies better good, says Yike."

Watch Yike's QUT story  ❯<http://links.realworld.qut.edu.au/ctt?ms=NjQ2ODgxODUS1&kn=2&r=MzUzNDI2NTU2NjA4S0&b=0&j=MTg4MDk1Njc2NgS2&mt=1&rt=0>

Hi Jimena,

Great to hear from you again! My name is Alie and I'm here to help answer any questions you may have.

Our portal is open all year round, so you can apply at any time and applications can take up to 30 days for assessment.

We recommend applying at least 4 months in advance of the start date to allow enough time for applying for a visa (if required).

The application closing date for students not in Australia is typically 4 weeks before the start of class. The 2025 deadlines have not yet been confirmed.

Hi Jimena,

Great to hear from you and I’m glad to hear you’re interested in study at QUT! My name is Morgan and I'm here to help answer any questions you may have.

Our Master of Robotics and Artificial Intelligence<https://www.qut.edu.au/courses/master-of-robotics-and-artificial-intelligence> commences in February of each academic year and runs for 1.5 years full-time from our Gardens Point campus. The annual international tuition fee is approximately $41,700 (2024 AUD fees).

To view the entry requirements<https://www.qut.edu.au/courses/master-of-robotics-and-artificial-intelligence?international#requirements>, visit the course page and scroll down to the ‘Explore this course’ section and click on the ‘Requirements’ tab.

Additional requirements include:

  *   A completed recognised four-year full time Bachelor degree in Engineering in one of the following fields or equialvent: Computer and Software Systems, Electrical, Aerospace, Electronics or Mechatronics with a GPA minimum of 4.0 (on QUT's 7-point scale).

Accommodation and living in Brisbane
During your first weeks in Brisbane, you should budget for approximately $2,500AUD to get yourself set-up in your accommodation, stock up on food and organise your transport card. After that, you can budget for approximately $500 a week for rent, food, transport, utility bills and entertainment.

You’ll find a wide range of accommodation options<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/student-life/living-in-brisbane/accommodation-in-brisbane?international> to suit all budgets within walking distance to either campus. QUT has a dedicated accommodation support service<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/qut.studystays.com.au/__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CHlKcaajZa80ZbH5aBkKUe-qOjWeU2Xs55OGqtR33Y8rZSwIQbmSo9HVUirkTMqLb6Q6F4qux7h43tG_REehMUgB$> to help you navigate the rental market and get you settled into life in Brisbane.

You can read more about Living in Brisbane<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/student-life/living-in-brisbane?international> on the website.

I believe I have answered all your questions but if you need additional support, you can reply to this email, call us, chat with us, or book a call back<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/bit.ly/3LtsKxj__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CHlKcaajZa80ZbH5aBkKUe-qOjWeU2Xs55OGqtR33Y8rZSwIQbmSo9HVUirkTMqLb6Q6F4qux7h43tG_RIXVlS68$>.

Kind regards,
Morgan

Hi Minila,
Congratulations on receiving an offer to study at QUT!

We’re delighted to have you join us next semester. There’s just one last step to secure your place!

To accept your offer, head to the Application Portal<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://bit.ly/InternationalApplyNow__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!E0fc_EQlhZt8O_wEg9OWtjr56uEoEo9TGANDcw4qJAAyQicHJOHApf33PGhAyth0147XDvjm5ru2cUqJLJhvPg$> and select ‘Respond to offer’. Click ‘Accept’ and complete the acceptance of offer form.

Don’t forget you’ll have to accept your offer at least two weeks prior to the start date listed in your offer letter. We recommend accepting as soon as you can to ensure you have enough time to apply for your visa, attend orientation and prepare for study!

If you need any further assistance accepting your offer, or you’re not sure what to do, you can reach out to our Future Students team via email, phone, WhatsApp or you can book a call back<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://bit.ly/3LtsKxj__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!E0fc_EQlhZt8O_wEg9OWtjr56uEoEo9TGANDcw4qJAAyQicHJOHApf33PGhAyth0147XDvjm5ru2cUo4-_TSnw$>.

We look forward to seeing you on campus!

Kind regards,
International Future Students

Subject: Regarding Offer Letter for Master's in Information Technology
Description:
Dear QUT,

I hope this message finds you well. My name is Sharath Badrinath and I am writing to express my concern regarding the status of my application for the Master's in Information Technology program at Queensland University of Technology.

I submitted my application approximately two months ago and, regrettably, I have not yet received my offer letter. As the February intake is rapidly approaching, I am eager to initiate the necessary preparations for the upcoming semester.

I understand that various factors contribute to the application review process, and I appreciate the efforts of the admissions team. However, given the proximity of the February intake, I kindly request your assistance in expediting the processing of my application and issuing the offer letter at the earliest convenience.

I am enthusiastic about the prospect of joining QUT and am keen to commence my studies in Information Technology.

I appreciate your attention to this matter and your understanding of the time sensitivity involved. I look forward to your prompt response and guidance on the next steps.

Thank you for your assistance.

Sincerely,

Sharath Badrinath
 Application ID -  6735729

Find your people at QUT
Whether you are missing home or excited to go on a new adventure there's supportive and exciting communities around every corner at QUT.

Join the QUT surfers club and travel down to the stunning coast of Byron Bay to learn how to surf. If you prefer to surf powder, join the QUT snowsports club and go on their annual trip to NZ to hit the slopes.

There are special interest groups covering bubble tea, anime and manga, burlesque, Minecraft and so much more.

There are also faculty-specific clubs to help you with all things relevant to your degree, and associations for many countries providing support and a sense of home.

Great to hear from you and I’m glad to hear you’re interested in study at QUT! My name is Alie and I'm here to help answer any questions you may have.

If you have completed a degree in English, in an approved English-speaking country this can certainly be considered towards meeting the English language proficiency requirement for the QUT program. Approved English-speaking countries are Australia, Canada, England, Ireland, New Zealand, Scotland, South Africa, United States of America and Wales. To have your qualifications assessed, you will need to submit a formal application with your supporting documents to be considered for English language exemption based on prior studies completed in English.

If you have not completed prior learning in an approved English-speaking country, you can still apply without an English proficiency test and our admissions team can assess your application for an English language exemption. Please note this may result in application processing delays.

Applying to QUT
Applying is easy! Just head to our Application Portal<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://bit.ly/InternationalApplyNow__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!FcwgwXzXF0wQoHY-u-CtqhxP9jsHWMZSmOT8AaP9zynPu8zelmYYc3YEZL2-xAuR2Zj6SGnB5ScGs9oIOMPU$> and create an account. From there, you'll be able to start your application process. Don't forget to include all the necessary documents like your high school completion certificate/academic transcripts, English language proficiency test results, and passport identity page. We look forward to reviewing your application!

I believe I have answered all your questions but if you need additional support, you can reply to this email, call us, chat with us, or book a call back<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://bit.ly/3LtsKxj__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!FcwgwXzXF0wQoHY-u-CtqhxP9jsHWMZSmOT8AaP9zynPu8zelmYYc3YEZL2-xAuR2Zj6SGnB5ScGs6fifCgN$>.

Description:
Dear Sir, It’s my pleasure to inform you that I would like to study biotechnology at your world-renowned Queensland University of Technology as an undergraduate student. I am a Bangladeshi student who completed the Higher Secondary School Certificate
ZjQcmQRYFpfptBannerStart
This Message Is From an Untrusted Sender
You have not previously corresponded with this sender.

ZjQcmQRYFpfptBannerEnd

Dear Sir,

It’s my pleasure to inform you that I would like to study biotechnology at your world-renowned Queensland University of Technology as an undergraduate student.

I am a Bangladeshi student who completed the Higher Secondary School Certificate (HSC) examination this year, in February 2023. In my Secondary School Certificate (SSC) and Higher Secondary School Certificate (HSC), my results are respectively GPA 5 and 4.17 out of GPA 5.

With the blessings of the internet and my teachers in schools and colleges, I came to know that the universities of the Australia provide high-quality education to students. Besides, Australia is one of the pioneers in education and technology in the world. So, I have decided to learn biotechnology at a world-class university from Australia. As I want to be a biotechnologist, I believe that after completing my study in biotechnology at Queensland University of Technology I will be able to become a world-known biotechnologist and enlighten the world with my light of knowledge as well as serve the humankind selflessly.

I have visited the website of Queensland University of Technology. There are so many photos of the beautiful campus and student activities of Queensland University of Technology. All of those have attracted me to study at Queensland University of Technology. Moreover, the university is located in Queensland, which is good, and the weather is also suitable for me.

I would be highly pleased if you could please provide me with the following information:

  1.  Admission requirements for undergraduate admission in biotechnology .

  2.  Admission procedures.

  3.  Course details.

  4.  Can I select multiple subjects in the admission form or change my course after admission?

  5.  Sessions/application start and deadline.

  6.  Do international students have to take any particular test?

  7.  Eligibility for getting a scholarship.

  8.  Which extracurricular activities are recommended?

  9.  Admission application fees (and the way of waive this fee, if possible)

  10. Admission fees.

  11. Total semesters and tuition fee for each semester

  12. Do I have to send any money to the university after getting the offer letter?

  13. How much funding do I need to show for a student visa?

  14. Permission to work elsewhere to manage tuition fees.

  15. Facilities for international students.

  16. Recommend an expert or a professor who can guide me in this situation (please, include his/ her email address).

  17. Other information, if you think to include it, will help me get more ideas.

I have contacted Australia embassy officials in Dhaka. They have informed me that if I can get admitted to a Australian university, the embassy will issue me a student visa.

I have attached copies of my SSC, HSC, and other additional transcripts and documents with this email.

It would be a great pleasure for me if you sent me an email with detailed information about whether I am eligible or not. My detailed information is given below. I am looking forward to getting a reply from you.

Sincerely yours,

Mohammod Soaib Hasan Alvi

Mailing address: House No. 74/19, Block A, Bank Colony, Savar, Dhaka, Bangladesh

Subject: Re: Meegha, your future starts now!
Description:
Respected Sir/Ma'am,

I am Meegha Jerry, a student from India. I've applied to study Master of nursing- (entry to practice) program in QUT. My QUT student number is 11817429.
On July 13, 2023, I received the conditional offer letter, and I submitted all of the required documents.The agency advised me that until I had the unconditional offer letter, I couldn't submit my SOP and financial documents. It wasn't until November that I received the unconditional offer. That does, however, state that I can only begin my studies in 2025. I applied for the February 2024 intake, and THE CONDITIONAL offer letter specifically states that the course begins on February 26, 2024.Upon inquiry into the reason behind the 2024 commencement year switch to 2025 ,i discovered that I will not be able to enrol in my course in 2024 as seats are already filled.

Having applied early this year, as well as promptly responding to the conditional offer letter by accepting it and submitting all the necessary documents, I don't think it's fair that I have to wait so long to receive an unconditional offer letter stating that I can only start in 2025 .with all due respect, I felt that this was unjust and that I deserve the opportunity to study in 2024.It is impossible for me to wait until 2025 to enroll in this course as I'll have a long academic gap and negatively affect me in various ways.

I might be just one among the numerous students that apply in your university. However, for me, this is my ideal course and university, this is my life.I've spent the last few months getting acquainted with the fundamentals of human biology in order to be a top student at your university. Becoming a student at QUT is my dream and the most important thing to me. I genuinely believe that I will contribute positively to your university. If I can only enrol in the course in 2025, I sadly won’t be able to study at QUT. If I can only enrol in the course in 2025, I sadly won't be able to study at my dream university QUT.
With a heavy heart and much hope, I humbly request that you grant me the chance to enrol in my desired course in 2024. Could you please kindly change my commencement year from 2025 to 2024 and assess my application for 2024.
Eagerly and anxiously awaiting your favourable reply.


Thank you.

You have an offer with QUT! 🎉
Hi Meegha,

Congratulations on your unconditional offer to study Master of Nursing - Entry to Practice at QUT in Semester 1, 2025!

We are so excited to have you join us and the other thousands of international students in Brisbane. You can accept your offer now by getting in touch with your agent, KC Overseas Education.

Remember to accept early so you leave plenty of time to organise everything before classes start.
Email your agent ❯ <mailto:australia5@studies-overseas.com?subject=Application%20Enquiry>
[https://image.connectme.qut.edu.au/lib/fe3111717164067d761d76/m/1/feb87eb5-672e-4153-b35b-08a94140cec5.jpg]
Find your people at QUT
Whether you are missing home or excited to go on a new adventure there's supportive and exciting communities around every corner at QUT.

Join the QUT surfers club and travel down to the stunning coast of Byron Bay to learn how to surf. If you prefer to surf powder, join the QUT snowsports club and go on their annual trip to NZ to hit the slopes.

There are special interest groups covering bubble tea, anime and manga, burlesque, Minecraft and so much more.

There are also faculty-specific clubs to help you with all things relevant to your degree, and associations for many countries providing support and a sense of home.

No matter what your interests or needs, there is a QUT club to support you. And if there's not - you can always start one!

Subject: Master of nursing- (entry to practice) application
Description:
Respected Sir/Ma'am,

I am Meegha Jerry, a student from India. I've applied to study Master of nursing- (entry to practice) program in QUT. My QUT student number is 11817429.
On July 13, 2023, I received the conditional offer letter, and I submitted all of the required documents.The agency advised me that until I had the unconditional offer letter, I couldn't submit my SOP and financial documents. It wasn't until November that I received the unconditional offer. That does, however, state that I can only begin my studies in 2025. I applied for the February 2024 intake, and THE CONDITIONAL offer letter specifically states that the course begins on February 26, 2024.Upon inquiry into the reason behind the 2024 commencement year switch to 2025 ,i discovered that I will not be able to enrol in my course in 2024 as seats are already filled.

Having applied early this year, as well as promptly responding to the conditional offer letter by accepting it and submitting all the necessary documents, I don't think it's fair that I have to wait so long to receive an unconditional offer letter stating that I can only start in 2025 .with all due respect, I felt that this was unjust and that I deserve the opportunity to study in 2024.It is impossible for me to wait until 2025 to enroll in this course as I'll have a long academic gap and negatively affect me in various ways.

I might be just one among the numerous students that apply in your university. However, for me, this is my ideal course and university, this is my life.I've spent the last few months getting acquainted with the fundamentals of human biology in order to be a top student at your university. Becoming a student at QUT is my dream and the most important thing to me. I genuinely believe that I will contribute positively to your university. If I can only enrol in the course in 2025, I sadly won’t be able to study at QUT. If I can only enrol in the course in 2025, I sadly won't be able to study at my dream university QUT.

With a heavy heart and much hope, I humbly request that you grant me the chance to enrol in my desired course in 2024. Could you please kindly change my commencement year from 2025 to 2024 and assess my application for 2024.
Eagerly and anxiously awaiting your favourable reply.

Hi Charles,

Applications to study at QUT—the university for the real world—are open! Find out how to apply<https://click.connectme.qut.edu.au/?qs=153cc443c3c50485cf1811b7da2360bdae75c652cd3eb4b870f47701b206902629c08b81fb621b7bb3ce9c2a9af99e6e48851ecfdb72c08f3f80c4023cdf9584> so you can submit your application by Monday 22 January 2024 (Brisbane time) to be considered for study in February 2024.

I hope this email finds you well. My name is Syed Muzammil Hussain, and I am writing to express my gratitude for the opportunity to pursue my Masters in Professional Engineering (EN55) at Queensland University of Technology, Gardens Point. It is an honor to have been offered a place in the program.

I am excited about the prospect of studying at your esteemed institution; however, I am facing financial challenges as an international student from India. Due to the cost of tuition, living expenses, and other associated costs, it would be extremely helpful for me to secure a scholarship to support my education.

I would like to request your consideration for a scholarship to assist with the financial aspects of my studies. I believe that with the help of a scholarship, I can fully dedicate myself to my academic pursuits and make the most of the learning opportunities provided by your university.

I am committed to academic excellence and have a strong track record of performance in my previous studies. I am confident that I can contribute positively to the university community. Being granted a scholarship would make a significant difference in my ability to focus on my studies and succeed in my chosen field.

If there are any specific scholarship programs available for international students in the field of Master of Professional Engineering (EN55), I kindly request information on how I can apply or be considered for such opportunities.

I understand the competitive nature of scholarship applications and appreciate your time and consideration of my request. I am happy to provide any additional documentation or information that may be required to evaluate my candidacy for a scholarship.

Thank you for your attention, and I look forward to your response. Please feel free to contact me if you need any further details or have any questions.

Sincerely,

Syed Muzammil Hussain

Hi Autakorn,

Great to hear from you and I’m glad to hear you’re interested in study at QUT! My name is Morgan and I'm here to help answer any questions you may have.

If you have completed a degree in English, in an approved English-speaking country this can certainly be considered towards meeting the English language proficiency requirement for the QUT program. Approved English-speaking countries are Australia, Canada, England, Ireland, New Zealand, Scotland, South Africa, United States of America and Wales. To have your qualifications assessed, you will need to submit a formal application with your supporting documents to be considered for English language exemption based on prior studies completed in English.

For specific English Language requirements, check the Entry Requirements tab on the course page. You can select the Unites States and view the qualifications you must have completed to be eligible for an exemption.

Applications to study at QUT—the university for the real world—are open! [QUT logo]
[QUT City]
Let me tell you about my experience.
Hi Adeline,

My name is Vine and two years ago I was right where you are now – deciding which university to trust with my future.

After receiving offers to study at three different universities, I was struggling to choose which one to accept. There were so many factors to consider like educational culture and areas of expertise, so after researching and asking lots of questions to all three universities, I chose QUT – the university for the real world.

During my two years studying at QUT, I was constantly impressed by how QUT emphasised opportunities that integrated knowledge and learnings into real, high-quality practical applications. Each project or assessment was grounded and embedded with real-world examples, giving real insight into how companies and organisations worked to solve challenges.

But it’s not all about study. I have also worked part-time in hospitality and retail, explored Brisbane, and made lots of friends. The experiences I have gained have helped me to become more independent and confident.

I understand that making the decision to study overseas is a big decision, but it’s also a brave one. My advice? Step outside your comfort zone and challenge yourself.

Best wishes on your journey to QUT!

Vine
Master of Business (Marketing), China

Hi Julian,



Great to hear from you and I’m glad to hear you’re interested in study at QUT! My name is Morgan and I'm here to help answer any questions you may have.



Credit for prior learning

To be considered for credit towards your QUT course and be able to graduate sooner, you will need to include additional supporting documents with your application. This includes:



  *   your official academic transcript showing the unit code(s), unit title(s) and grade(s) achieved
  *   documents proving that you have completed your course, such as a completion certificate
  *   unit outlines or course syllabus of the unit(s) you are wanting credit for.



There is a question within the application called “Do you wish to be considered for Advanced Standing based on your previous studies?”. You will need to select ‘Yes’ to this question.



Once you have finished and submitted your application, our international admission team will consider your request for advanced standing. Details of the credit awarded and the potential reduction in course duration will be listed in your QUT offer letter. We cannot pre-assess credit – you must apply to QUT with your supporting documents for consideration.



You can search for previously approved units<https://www.advancedstanding.qut.edu.au/cgi-bin/WebObjects/AdvStand.woa> for credit on the Advanced Standing Precedent List.



Applying to QUT

When you’re ready to apply, head to our Application Portal<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://bit.ly/InternationalApplyNow__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!C98BojIyggo-5VFh-7iYeiceXty2BHSGEfHV9-noIXIKyvbmDcCQAWT0LTSTazOoUVm6glp0gf5dPG6HharoZoH27Ung2t1Jdw$> and create an account. From there, you'll be able to start your application process. Don't forget to include all the necessary documents like your high school completion certificate/academic transcripts, English language proficiency test results, and passport identity page. We look forward to reviewing your application!



Scholarships

All international applicants are automatically considered for the International Merit Scholarship (IMS) once an application has been submitted. The IMS award offers a 25% reduction in tuition fees for the first year of your course at QUT.



For eligible courses only, an ongoing award of 25% per semester may be offered to students who continue to meet the GPA requirement.



For more information, please visit the International Merit Scholarship<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/fees-and-scholarships/scholarships/international-merit-scholarship> webpage.
