Let me tell you about my experience.



Hi Edward,

My name is Vine and two years ago I was right where you are now – deciding which university to trust with my future.

After receiving offers to study at three different universities, I was struggling to choose which one to accept. There were so many factors to consider like educational culture and areas of expertise, so after researching and asking lots of questions to all three universities, I chose QUT – the university for the real world.

During my two years studying at QUT, I was constantly impressed by how QUT emphasised opportunities that integrated knowledge and learnings into real, high-quality practical applications. Each project or assessment was grounded and embedded with real-world examples, giving real insight into how companies and organisations worked to solve challenges.

But it’s not all about study. I have also worked part-time in hospitality and retail, explored Brisbane, and made lots of friends. The experiences I have gained have helped me to become more independent and confident.

I understand that making the decision to study overseas is a big decision, but it’s also a brave one. My advice? Step outside your comfort zone and challenge yourself.

Best wishes on your journey to QUT!

Vine
Master of Business (Marketing), China

El 27-10-2023, a las 01:31, QUT International Future Students <qut.direct@qut.edu.au<mailto:qut.direct@qut.edu.au>> escribió:



<image001.png>





Hi Pamela,

Great to hear from you and I’m glad to hear you’re interested in study at QUT! My name is Alie and I'm here to help answer any questions you may have.

Our portal is open all year round, so you can apply at any time.

We recommend applying at least 4 months in advance of the start date to allow enough time for applying for a visa (if required).

The application closing date for students not in Australia is typically 4 weeks before the start of class. For Semester 1, 2024 this date is the 29 January.

Our Bachelor of Design (Fashion)<https://www.qut.edu.au/courses/bachelor-of-design-fashion> commences inFebruary, July of each academic year and runs for 3 years full-time from our Kelvin Grove campus. The international tuition fee is approximately $35,200 per year full-time (2024 AUD fees).

To view the entry requirements<https://www.qut.edu.au/courses/bachelor-of-design-fashion?international#requirements>, visit the course page and scroll down to the ‘Explore this course’ section and click on the ‘Requirements’ tab. Use the drop-down menu to select your country to view the qualification requirements. If your country or qualifications are not listed, you can still apply for this course and our international admission team will assess your eligibility once you have submitted a formal application. We cannot pre-assess qualifications.

Applying to QUT
Applying is easy! Just head to our Application Portal<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://bit.ly/InternationalApplyNow__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!GK-ypn19fv0mA-hhVqY71xwSw8bg18aHxyB5-GRvAISqtsIBRUsesu6yltqGoCdODjAdKdIDRJNI5d2vzWF_47rYMbYNE3G4yA$>and create an account. From there, you'll be able to start your application process. Don't forget to include all the necessary documents like your high school completion certificate/academic transcripts, English language proficiency test results, and passport identity page. We look forward to reviewing your application!

I believe I have answered all your questions but if you need additional support, you can reply to this email, call us, chat with us, or book a call back<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://bit.ly/3LtsKxj__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!GK-ypn19fv0mA-hhVqY71xwSw8bg18aHxyB5-GRvAISqtsIBRUsesu6yltqGoCdODjAdKdIDRJNI5d2vzWF_47rYMbabtrdwIw$>.

Kind regards,
Alie

Subject: Re: Ready to start your journey?
Description:
Thank you so much for the great news!

On Fri, 17 Nov, 2023, 6:30 am QUT International, <qut.direct@connectme.qut.edu.au<mailto:qut.direct@connectme.qut.edu.au>> wrote:
It's time to accept your offer!

Can't see the images? View as webpage.<https://view.connectme.qut.edu.au/?qs=4a30665ad1c2cd72bd2fb841e75ce18824ef6cc693369f6502f8cbd2bdca5dec5d696d41c7b69dab9e0c74d2d3414050832cbf47d90312f969bfd576567dec364fcf151a3bb876121f2eacf643045301>
[QUT logo]
[https://image.connectme.qut.edu.au/lib/fe3111717164067d761d76/m/1/084fbb44-e4d7-42f9-a84b-17c47ce4d355.jpg]
Here's how to accept and join us at QUT
Accepting your offer to study will be exciting and a little daunting at first. Here is a list of what happens next so you can feel prepared and ready to take on this next journey with confidence.

  *   Meet all the conditions outlined on your offer letter and then ask your agent to accept your offer. Don't forget to pay your deposit as we won't be able to process your acceptance until we have received your payment. You'll need to contact your agent to complete this step.
  *   We will aim to process your acceptance within 5 business days and provide your agent with your Confirmation of Enrolment Certificate (eCOE).
  *   When you are accepted, you can access a whole range of great resources to get you started at QUT, including enrolment guides, class registration instructions, timetable planning, support and more!

Ready to get started?
Email your agent ❯ <mailto:info.patiala@idp.com?subject=Application%20Enquiry>
[https://image.connectme.qut.edu.au/lib/fe3111717164067d761d76/m/1/93f7c225-20e1-4c72-860d-9b55f8fb3c2a.jpg]
Support for your journey
We provide international students with quality support services, helpful information and advice to enhance their studies at QUT.

Whether you need help preparing to move to Brisbane, support whilst studying, or even some friendly tips on the best recreational activities in Queensland, we are here to help.
Join the international student community ❯ <https://click.connectme.qut.edu.au/?qs=8b0bfaff60a749317ce9b119f2339ffac1f5bfea4f3310f955242969d26da5890b02ca992de67224b5c7f6d915508fc0bd9606386f578af0>

Dear Admissions Committee,

I trust this message finds you well. I am writing to express my sincere gratitude for the conditional offer extended to me for the Master's program at QUT (Queensland University of Technology). The prospect of contributing to your esteemed institution's academic community is truly exciting.

In light of the conditional offer, I respectfully request a waiver of the IELTS test score requirement for my application. My academic and professional background reflects a robust command of the English language, positioning me for success in the Master's program.

Having pursued my undergraduate studies in Australia, I immersed myself in an English-speaking environment and achieved academic excellence. Currently enrolled in the Master's program in Healthcare Administration at Saudi Electronic University, I have further refined my English language skills through an exclusively English-medium curriculum, as confirmed by an official letter from the institution.

Furthermore, my seven years of dedicated experience as a healthcare professional have involved extensive communication in English with colleagues, patients, and stakeholders. This professional journey has not only enriched my linguistic abilities but has also equipped me to engage in complex discussions, meticulously document medical records, and seamlessly provide patient care in an English-speaking work environment.

Considering the depth of my academic and professional experiences, I kindly request the Admissions Committee at QUT to consider waiving the IELTS test score requirement, acknowledging my demonstrated proficiency in the English language.

In addition to the waiver request, I express my eagerness for the conversion of my conditional offer into an unconditional one. I am confident that my background aligns seamlessly with the expectations of the Master's program at QUT, and I am fully committed to contributing meaningfully to this academic endeavor.

Thank you for dedicating your time to consider my request. I look forward with enthusiasm to the prospect of contributing to the QUT community and the opportunity to immerse myself in the Master's program.

Response By Email (Jessica) (18/11/2023 09.53 AM)


Hi Anupriya,

Thanks so much for your email. I can certainly help with your enquiry regarding admission pathways.

For domestic students who are interested in studying an undergraduate degree and who do not have an ATAR, a selection rank can be used in order to assess eligibility for a course. When course offers are made, selection ranks and ATARs are treated equally, and selection ranks can be obtained a number of ways.

Below I have provided some general information on these admission pathways for you. You may also like to look over our online Admission pathways booklet<https://cms.qut.edu.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0012/252021/qut-admission-pathways-guide.pdf> for further information.

Entry Based on Secondary Education
Year 12 results don't expire after you finish school. They are converted to a selection rank and you can continue to use them to get into university in the future. If you completed any of the following, your experience there can be translated into a selection rank, which can then be used to gain entry into a course:

  *
An International Baccalaureate Diploma (IBD)
  *
A vocational education and training (VET) qualification completed at school (certificate IV or above)
  *
Seventh grade AMEB (or higher) or equivalent qualifications.

You may like to look over our Recent secondary education<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/applying/recent-secondary-education> page for more information if this is relevant to you.

Vocational Education and Training (VET) Study
VET study can provide a great foundation for future study at QUT.  To be considered for entry to degree courses you can use an Australian Qualifications Framework (AQF) award completed at TAFE or a private education provider, including:

  *
Certificate IV
  *
Diploma
  *
Advanced diploma.

Completion of VET studies can then be used to translate into a selection rank, which can then be used to gain entry into a course. Please note that a certificate III can only be used to gain entry into a QUT Diploma, and not an undergraduate course.

I would recommend having a look over our VET study<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/applying/vet-study> page for more information on this admission pathway and to see how these studies can translate into a selection rank.

Work and Life Experience
Work and life experience can be assessed in order to obtain a selection rank, which can then be used to gain entry into a course. This selection rank will be based on your professional qualifications, paid employment, or past school results.

I would recommend having a look at our Work and life experience<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/applying/work-and-life-experience> page for more information on this admission pathway.

Applying
When it comes to the application for the course, for admission into our undergraduate courses you'll need to apply online through the Queensland Tertiary Admissions Centre (QTAC)<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://www.qtac.edu.au/__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!DZxwYJEpoAUOEFEerpHgKFpQb9xFIrjeZPgLMJM-0xd1TyHgm3gZmQjnbpfvR5r09te0UtJKbBsb1TJtHfzYt1Q$>.

You'll need to meet specific entry requirements for your application to be considered, check requirements for courses on the QUT website<https://www.qut.edu.au/study>.

Once you've submitted your application, QTAC will assess it and you may receive an offer.

When you're ready to apply for a course, follow our step-by-step applying guide<https://www.qut.edu.au/study/applying/undergraduate-guide> for undergraduate courses.

Unique Student Identifier (USI)
QUT students will need to provide a USI. The process to getting one is quite simple, you will just need to apply for one through the Australian Government<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://www.usi.gov.au/__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!DZxwYJEpoAUOEFEerpHgKFpQb9xFIrjeZPgLMJM-0xd1TyHgm3gZmQjnbpfvR5r09te0UtJKbBsb1TJtkEgwYck$> website.

I hope this information has helped to answer your enquiry, however please let us know if you need any additional information or clarification. Additionally, please let us know if there are any specific courses you are interested in and we can provide more information on those course entry requirements.

If there’s anything else we can help you with, please reply to this email, call us on (07) 3138 2000, visit us on campus<http://www.qut.edu.au/student-centres> or start an online chat<https://www.qut.edu.au/about/contact/hiq-chat>.

Your reference number is: 231117-000414

Kind regards,
Jessica

Hi Miki,

Thank you for your enquiry and congratulations on receiving an offer to study at QUT. My name is Morgan and I can help answer any questions you have.

You will select your major when you enrol in your units in your first semester.

Congratulations on receiving the scholarship! Your total tuition and acceptance deposit will be reduced with the scholarship amount. The $12,750 acceptance deposit has already been reduced based on your scholarship. This deposit covers your first semester of study at QUT. You will need to pay your fees upfront again at the start of your second semester.

The acceptance deadline is generally 2 weeks before the start of the semester, however we suggest accepting as soon as possible so that you can begin organising your visa, accommodation and get ready to move to Australia to study. The exact date has not yet been confirmed.

I believe I have answered all your questions but if you need additional support, you can reply to this email, call us, chat with us, or book a call back<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/bit.ly/3LtsKxj__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!FnP-lqOV6eSFR4oLtTOiVYqLTof1UQ6xHWmTtkXmEsw4qP7fl-FRjmJ7dMNc9afGlfV6Mc6xVDik3Y6mGl4LJA$>.

Subject: CloudStor Decommission - important information for users
Description:
[https://support.aarnet.edu.au/hc/article_attachments/6685303899151]

Dear CloudStor User,

This is a reminder that AARNet is decommissioning CloudStor at 12pm AEDT on 15 December 2023. You will need to download or move your data to an alternative service<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://support.aarnet.edu.au/hc/en-us/articles/6547506369679-Download-or-migrate-data-from-CloudStor__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CFewIEvPj3Su3S78obHIA56c4CHF0ar6j21p1dRb8HWVO95iyorbkoUpz7Tm0_mHt5Z86YEDTzSG2tN_XWU5PNPlgg-t$> before then.

From 15 December 2023 you will no longer be able to retrieve your data from CloudStor and AARNet will cease providing the CloudStor service to you, as per our terms and conditions<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://www.aarnet.edu.au/uploads/resources/CloudStor-End-User-service-terms-v1.1.pdf__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CFewIEvPj3Su3S78obHIA56c4CHF0ar6j21p1dRb8HWVO95iyorbkoUpz7Tm0_mHt5Z86YEDTzSG2tN_XWU5PJTbV1Zi$>.

To help you with this process, the following two features are available in CloudStor via a web browser.

Request All My Data

The Request All My Data feature can be used to create a copy of your CloudStor data. Once your request has been processed, you will receive an email with the link to download your data.

Learn more about how to request all your data<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://support.aarnet.edu.au/hc/en-us/articles/7303040651151-Request-All-My-Data__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CFewIEvPj3Su3S78obHIA56c4CHF0ar6j21p1dRb8HWVO95iyorbkoUpz7Tm0_mHt5Z86YEDTzSG2tN_XWU5PMPVpdx8$>

Delete My Account

You can use the Delete My Account feature to have your CloudStor account disabled and queued for removal after 15 December, 2023. Once you complete this process, you will no longer have access to CloudStor.

Learn more about how to delete your account<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://support.aarnet.edu.au/hc/en-us/articles/7302914897039-Delete-My-Account__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CFewIEvPj3Su3S78obHIA56c4CHF0ar6j21p1dRb8HWVO95iyorbkoUpz7Tm0_mHt5Z86YEDTzSG2tN_XWU5PFYkRLTi$>

Zoom Recordings

Zoom recordings you have stored on CloudStor will not be accessible after 15 December, 2023. From this date, you will no longer be able to download Zoom recordings from CloudStor or access them using the link that you received via email when the recording was first created.

We recommend that you download your Zoom recordings before 15 December 2023 using the CloudStor desktop app<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://support.aarnet.edu.au/hc/en-us/articles/7349971543567-Use-the-CloudStor-desktop-app-to-download-Zoom-recordings__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CFewIEvPj3Su3S78obHIA56c4CHF0ar6j21p1dRb8HWVO95iyorbkoUpz7Tm0_mHt5Z86YEDTzSG2tN_XWU5PI5ZDrZq$> or Rclone<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://support.aarnet.edu.au/hc/en-us/articles/7350141882511-Use-Rclone-to-download-Zoom-recordings__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CFewIEvPj3Su3S78obHIA56c4CHF0ar6j21p1dRb8HWVO95iyorbkoUpz7Tm0_mHt5Z86YEDTzSG2tN_XWU5PESHUNbx$>.

Learn more about Zoom recordings in CloudStor<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://support.aarnet.edu.au/hc/en-us/sections/7349084639119-Zoom-Recordings__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CFewIEvPj3Su3S78obHIA56c4CHF0ar6j21p1dRb8HWVO95iyorbkoUpz7Tm0_mHt5Z86YEDTzSG2tN_XWU5PIkvkCrb$>

CLOUDSTOR DECOMMISSION CLINICS – REGISTER NOW

This will be the final CloudStor Decommission Clinic held via Zoom in the lead up to the shutdown on 15 December 2023. These sessions are for information sharing and troubleshooting, with AARNet CloudStor support staff available to answer questions.

If you need help moving data from your CloudStor drive, come along to a CloudStor Decommission Clinic.

The next session is on 30 November 2023 at 1 pm AEDT.

Register for an upcoming CloudStor Decommission Clinic<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://aarnet.zoom.us/meeting/register/tZMof-qgqTkpE9f8s13ExpfqH2KZBnV2IaE9*/registration__;Iw!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CFewIEvPj3Su3S78obHIA56c4CHF0ar6j21p1dRb8HWVO95iyorbkoUpz7Tm0_mHt5Z86YEDTzSG2tN_XWU5PEMn1-Kq$>

More information

Why is AARNet decommissioning CloudStor?<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://support.aarnet.edu.au/hc/en-us/articles/5697089309711-Decommissioning-CloudStor-__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CFewIEvPj3Su3S78obHIA56c4CHF0ar6j21p1dRb8HWVO95iyorbkoUpz7Tm0_mHt5Z86YEDTzSG2tN_XWU5PHomra2V$>
How to download your data from CloudStor<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://support.aarnet.edu.au/hc/en-us/articles/6547506369679-Download-or-migrate-data-from-CloudStor__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CFewIEvPj3Su3S78obHIA56c4CHF0ar6j21p1dRb8HWVO95iyorbkoUpz7Tm0_mHt5Z86YEDTzSG2tN_XWU5PNPlgg-t$>
View the decommissioning FAQs<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://support.aarnet.edu.au/hc/en-us/sections/6547442372367-CloudStor-Decommission__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CFewIEvPj3Su3S78obHIA56c4CHF0ar6j21p1dRb8HWVO95iyorbkoUpz7Tm0_mHt5Z86YEDTzSG2tN_XWU5PPSyvJ_j$>
View the full timeline<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://support.aarnet.edu.au/hc/en-us/articles/6547482231439-CloudStor-decommission-timeline-__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CFewIEvPj3Su3S78obHIA56c4CHF0ar6j21p1dRb8HWVO95iyorbkoUpz7Tm0_mHt5Z86YEDTzSG2tN_XWU5PL7m5j0i$>
View more CloudStor FAQs<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://support.aarnet.edu.au/hc/en-us/sections/115000264394-FAQ__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CFewIEvPj3Su3S78obHIA56c4CHF0ar6j21p1dRb8HWVO95iyorbkoUpz7Tm0_mHt5Z86YEDTzSG2tN_XWU5PKFD6Z_U$>

If you have any questions, please contact cloudstor@aarnet.edu.au<mailto:cloudstor@aarnet.edu.au?subject=Re:%20AARNet%20is%20decommissioning%20CloudStor%20at%20the%20end%20of%202023&body=>.

Regards,
The CloudStor Team

You are receiving this email because you have a CloudStor account with AARNet.

Your privacy is important to us. AARNet is committed to protecting your privacy, managing your personal information in a secure environment and using your information for AARNet-related business purposes only. Our Privacy Policy<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://www.aarnet.edu.au/privacy-policy__;!!NVzLfOphnbDXSw!CFewIEvPj3Su3S78obHIA56c4CHF0ar6j21p1dRb8HWVO95iyorbkoUpz7Tm0_mHt5Z86YEDTzSG2tN_XWU5PEasTnZw$> describes how we manage any personal information we have about you.

Let me tell you about my experience.
Hi Barry,

My name is Vine and two years ago I was right where you are now – deciding which university to trust with my future.

After receiving offers to study at three different universities, I was struggling to choose which one to accept. There were so many factors to consider like educational culture and areas of expertise, so after researching and asking lots of questions to all three universities, I chose QUT – the university for the real world.

During my two years studying at QUT, I was constantly impressed by how QUT emphasised opportunities that integrated knowledge and learnings into real, high-quality practical applications. Each project or assessment was grounded and embedded with real-world examples, giving real insight into how companies and organisations worked to solve challenges.

But it’s not all about study. I have also worked part-time in hospitality and retail, explored Brisbane, and made lots of friends. The experiences I have gained have helped me to become more independent and confident.

I understand that making the decision to study overseas is a big decision, but it’s also a brave one. My advice? Step outside your comfort zone and challenge yourself.

Best wishes on your journey to QUT!

Vine
Master of Business (Marketing), China
